<TITLE> Police rescue 9 of a family abducted from Sutrapur home </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com)  Police rescued nine members of a family abducted from their house in the capital's Sutrapur area in the early hours of Saturday, by a gang allegedly working for a local property developer. Moniruzzaman Tuku, Dhaka Metropolitan Police assistant commissioner, told bdnews24.com four suspects had been arrested in connection with the incident. He said a gang of criminals, introducing themselves as policemen, went to the house at Hrishikesh Das Lane at around 3:30am. The criminals forced nine members of the family to leave the house at gunpoint and detained them at a nearby workshop, said Tuku. Police stormed the workshop, Janata Engineering Works, on information from locals and rescued the kidnapped family. Shambhu Das, the head of the family, told bdnews24.com that the criminals had beaten them. Das also alleged that the kidnappers were sent by a property developer that had been pressuring his family to strike a deal on their age-old three-storey building at Hrishikesh Das Lane. Police said they were looking into the matter. "The arrestees are being grilled," Tuku said. bd
